info.name: Kesar Pista Kulfi Falooda with Rabdi
info.description: Serves 1- A traditional Indian dessert combining saffron (kesar) and pistachio (pista) flavored kulfi with thin vermicelli noodles (falooda) and sweetened milk (rabdi). It's often garnished with chopped nuts and served chilled.

info.name: Bombay Special Falooda
info.description: Serves 1- Bombay falooda is a popular street food dessert in India. It typically consists of layers of flavored milk, falooda noodles, basil seeds, and ice cream, often garnished with nuts and rose syrup. It's known for its refreshing and indulgent taste.
